## How to work in this repo

This repo uses the **QRSPI multi-agent workflow** with human review gates. The setup lives in `.claude/`.

For complex changes:

| Command | What it does |
|---------|--------------|
| `/r <task>` | Gather facts about the affected code (no code changes) |
| `/d <task>` | Director runs the full QRSPI flow: research → design → plan → delegate → synthesize |
| `/iterate-research <feedback>` | Re-run research with corrective feedback (when you reject the research doc) |
| `/iterate-design <feedback>` | Re-run design with corrective feedback (when you reject the design doc) |
| `/verify` | Run typecheck + lint + build to validate a change after implementation |
| `/complete-plan` | Mark a plan complete and archive it to `plans/_done/` |

For simple changes (one-line fixes, doc tweaks, obvious renames), just edit directly — don't invoke the full pipeline.

The Director reads `.claude/agents/registry.md` to pick teams. Specialists live in `.claude/agents/<team>/`. See `.claude/agents/director.md` for the full flow and `.claude/agents/registry.md` for the team roster.

